            <div class="left wow fadeInDown" id="tab4">
                <h2>Treatment Techniques</h2>
                <p class="lead">The Prostate cancer can be treated by various treatment techniques depending on the stage of the cancer. <br /> </p>
                <p class="lead"><b><h3>Prescription</h3></b></p>
                <p class="lead"><b>Hormones:</b> Leuprorelin by injection (Lupron), Flutamide (Eulexin), Goserelin by injection (Zoladex), Bicalutamide (Casodex), Nilutamide (Nilandron) </p>
                <p class="lead"><b>Other treatments:</b> Dutasteride (Avodart), Docetaxel by injection (Docefrez), Abiraterone (Zytiga), Zoledronic acid by injection (Zometa), Cabazitaxel by injection </p>
                <p class="lead"><b><h3>Also common </h3></b></p>
                <p class="lead"><b>Procedures:</b> Robotic surgery, Prostatectomy, Radiation therapy, Laparoscopic surgery, Radical retropubic prostatectomy, Radiosurgery, Prostate brachytherapy, Laparoscopic radical prostatectomy, Particle therapy, Brachytherapy, External beam radiotherapy </p>
                <p class="lead"><b>Other treatments:</b> Monitoring of symptoms for change or improvement, Gonadotropin-Releasing hormone analogue, Hormone therapy </p>
                <p class="lead"><b><h3>Specialists </h3></b></p>
                <p class="lead"><b>Oncologist:</b> Specializes in cancer</p>
                <p class="lead"><b>Radiologist: </b> Uses images to diagnose and treat disease within the body. </p>
                <p class="lead"><b>Urologist: </b> Treats urinary tract diseases. </p>
                <p class="lead"><b>Radiation oncologist: </b> Treats and manages cancer by prescribing radiation therapy. </p>
                <p class="lead"><b>Surgeon:</b> Performs operations to treat disease. </p>
